  "response": "Since its independence in 1947, India has been involved in several wars with its neighboring countries:\n\n1. Indo-Pakistani War (1947-1948)\n- Outcome: Ended in a ceasefire, Kashmir divided between India and Pakistan\n\n2. Sino-Indian War (1962)\n- Outcome: Decisive Chinese victory, India lost territory in Himalayan region\n\n3. Indo-Pakistani War (1965)\n- Outcome: Inconclusive, ended with Tashkent Declaration\n\n4. Bangladesh Liberation War (1971)\n- Outcome: India supported Bangladesh's independence, Pakistan defeated\n\n5. Kargil War (1999)\n- Outcome: India successfully pushed back Pakistani intruders from Kargil sector\n\n6. Sino-Indian War (2020)\n- Outcome: Border skirmish in Galwan Valley, tensions remained high\n\nAdditionally, India has had several military confrontations and border skirmishes with:\n- China (1967 Nathu La and Cho La clashes)\n- Pakistan (multiple incidents along Line of Control)\n- Border tensions with Nepal and China\n\nThese conflicts have primarily been related to territorial disputes, particularly in Kashmir and Himalayan border regions.\n\nNote: This list covers major wars and significant military confrontations since independence.",
